            "id": "4af4999192744b7098b67",
            "questionText": "An astronaut with a mass of $!$m_A = 100\\,\\text{kg}$!$ is performing a spacewalk and accidentally collides with a piece of space debris with a mass of $!$m_D = 5\\,\\text{kg}$!$. Before the collision, the astronaut is stationary relative to the ISS, and the debris is moving at a velocity of $!$v_D = 8\\,\\text{m/s}$!$ towards her. Upon impact, the debris becomes embedded in the astronaut's suit. Assuming that the collision is completely inelastic, meaning the debris and the astronaut move together as one mass after the collision, determine the final velocity $!$v_f$!$ of the astronaut-debris system immediately after the impact.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "102e6860cd88475b84fbb",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by identifying the correct formula to calculate the momentum of an object. Which of the following formulas correctly represents momentum?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "c86c1ebf-b59a-4cec-8781-d933b9a8aeba"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$p = mv$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$p = m + v$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$p = m/v$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "24927dc217e942118d951",
                    "stepText": "Now that you have the momentum formula, calculate the momentum of the debris given its mass $!$m_D = 5\\,\\text{kg}$!$ and velocity $!$v_D = 8\\,\\text{m/s}$!$. What is the momentum of the debris?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "40"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "kg\u00b7m/s",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "c86c1ebf-b59a-4cec-8781-d933b9a8aeba"
                    ],
                    "options": []
                },
                {
                    "id": "9af8579afc7d4ab4be7a1",
                    "stepText": "Great, now determine the expression for the combined mass of the astronaut and the debris after the collision. Which of the following options correctly represents the combined mass?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [],
                    "options": [
