        {
            "id": "4112bd6cbb9c4b1db08ef",
            "questionText": "A rocket with an initial mass $!$M_0 = 5000\\,\\text{kg}$!$ is launched vertically upward. It expels exhaust gases at a constant speed of $!$u = 2500\\,\\text{m/s}$!$ relative to the rocket. During a short interval $!$\\Delta t = 0.1\\,\\text{s}$!$, the rocket burns and ejects $!$\\Delta m = 50\\,\\text{kg}$!$ of fuel. Determine the average thrust force exerted on the rocket during this time interval, due solely to the expulsion of the exhaust gases.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "bb1ec3af04484c088d23b",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by computing the mass flow rate. Given the change in mass $!$\\Delta m$!$ and the time interval $!$\\Delta t$!$, determine how you would calculate the mass flow rate.",
